FBIS3-35545 "drnes038dd_94031" FBIS-NES-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 Palestinian Affairs PLO Welcomes King Fahd's Campaign To Preserve Mosques LD2402233794 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 2200 GMT 23 Feb 94 LD2402233794 Algiers Voice of Palestine Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The Palestine Liberation Organization has welcomed the noble religious and humanitarian step by King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, the Servant of the Two Holy Places, and his permission to start a popular fund raising campaign at the level of all parts of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to renovate the Islamic sacrosancts in holy Jerusalem, and save them from a deliberate destruction due to the occupation measures that are aimed at wiping out the Islamic and Arab character of Jerusalem. To that end, His Royal Highness Prince Salman Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz has issued an appeal through the various information media to the citizens and residents of the Kingdom, urging them to make effective and generous contributions to save holy Jerusalem.
